latestPosts.caption:
This one’s for the moms who are healing while raising us.
We forget sometimes… they’re living life for the first time too.
We watch ourselves grow through phases, but rarely stop to notice — they’re growing too.

My mom didn’t just raise me.
She grew with me.
And in a world that told her to adjust… she taught me to adjust my crown instead.

If you’re lucky enough to be raised by a strong woman — you’ll know what I mean.
She may not have had all the answers.
She may have stayed silent when she should’ve spoken.
She may have tolerated more than she should’ve…
But with every fall, she taught me how to rise louder.

So here’s to the girl moms — raising daughters not to shrink for the sake of peace.
Not to compromise where there’s no respect.
Not to adjust in the name of love.

We’re breaking cycles — together.
And it’s about time we see them… not just as mothers,
but as women who are still learning to love, protect, and empower themselves too 🌷🤍✨

Twinning moment + OUTFIT CHECK 🤍🌸🕊️

Skirt: @studioanne.in 
Top: @onlyindia

Motherhood: the love that breaks you, builds you, and becomes you.

I never imagined I’d be doing motherhood alone.
But the day I found out I was pregnant, something inside me shifted.
From that moment on, every thought, every choice, every ounce of love — was for her.
It’s a love that began before we even met. And it changed me forever.

The truth is… motherhood is hard.
It’s exhausting, overwhelming, and lonely sometimes.
But it’s also the most powerful, grounding, soul-deep love I’ve ever known.
My daughter is my reason. My strength. My greatest blessing from Allah(swt)

Motherhood can be exhausting.
It can drain every part of you — physically, mentally, emotionally.
And yet, we show up. Every single day.
We pour love from a cup that barely feels full sometimes.
But we wouldn’t trade it for anything else in the world.

To every mother walking a tough path — solo parenting, health struggles, heartbreak, or just surviving the everyday chaos —
Please know this: you are not alone.
Your love, your strength, your quiet sacrifices — they matter.
And your child is watching.
They don’t need perfection — they need you.

Don’t wait to be told you’re doing a good job.
If you’re constantly second-guessing yourself,
it probably means you’re already giving your best.
Don’t wait for anyone to acknowledge or validate you.🌸
And PLEASE LOVE YOURSELF just as fiercely as you love your child.

Lastly, I couldn’t have done this alone.
To my mom, my sister, my friends, my family —
Thank you for being my strength, my village, and the arms that held me when I couldn’t hold myself.
You’ve helped me become the mother I am today.🥹🫶🏻

One day, inshaAllah, your child will grow up
and tell their friends, their partner, and their kids
that you were their safe place.
That you were their biggest blessing.
And that’s all that truly matters.

To every mom — I see you,I feel you,I’m with you.
Happy Mother’s Day-today and everyday 🤍

#happymothersday #soloparent #solomom #motherslove #motherdaughter
